SIMPLE: allonge
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Allonge
<hw>Al*longe"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>allonge</ets>, earlier <ets>alonge</ets>, a lengthening. See
<er>Allonge</er>, <pos>v.</pos>, and cf. <er>Lunge</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fencing)</fld> <def>A thrust or pass; a
lunge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slip of paper attached to a bill of exchange for
receiving indorsements, when the back of the bill itself is already
full; a rider.</def> <mark>[A French usage]</mark>
<rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allonge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Allonge
<hw>Al*longe"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>allonger</ets>;
<ets>⟦agrave⟧</ets> (L. <ets>ad</ets>) + <ets>long</ets> (L.
<ets>longus</ets>) long.]</ety> <def>To thrust with a sword; to
lunge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Allonym</ent>⟦br⟧
